name: Bao Express
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'If you looking for the correct style of food. Sorry, it is not. Fancy enough but nothing related to the food.

Their service was super quick, my dishes were delivered within 5 minutes after my order. All the food were cold when they arrivd my table.

Not tasty enough. The bun meat was dry and small portion, which a qualified meat bun shoul be meaty with juice. This style Chinese food should serve in hot and not pre cook.

At last, I am questioning about how the meat bun was made. You can saw that the bamboo steamer was dry compared to the Siumai one. The Siumai steamer was wet that mean at least the Siumai was steamed in it. Anyway, it was only my observation but mean nothing.', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I loved this place! In two weeks took the following: Chinese spring rolls (they were ok), Xiao Long Bao Shangai classic (the filling is very good and the dough is thick and fluffy), Char Siu Bao (basically the big dumplings, they are super tasty, I preferred these to the smaller ones), Aubergines Hong Shao (for sure the best thing we ate, they were delicious, I sincerely recommend these) and finally the Poulet Sweet & Sour (very good as well). We were very hungry and in the end we were quite full. Plus, the service was super kind and welcoming.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very very overrated, you can find better asian
restaurants in Paris. Never order the lemonade, it is just water. The mango sago is a mango lassi with very few tapioca perles and some small chunks of mango. Aubergines and noodles are ok.
Service was great. A shame that food wasn‚Äôt as good. Everything is deeply fried.', 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved this great place. üòã
Great food, options even for vegans.
Big place so you can be spontaneous, friendly staff.
Enjoy', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This has to be one of THE HIDDEN GEMS of Paris. This isn‚Äôt on any tourist lists of places to eat and it‚Äôs not typical French food, but it is delicious and the vibe in this place is immaculate. We enjoyed it so much, we went back on our last night in Paris to have it again!  Beef Ho Fun is easily the best dish we had in Paris and the Sweet and Sour Chicken is unlike any version we‚Äôve had in the best way possible. Also, if you‚Äôre a dessert person, the lava French toast is a must try!  We would eat here again and again and will recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: JJAN
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was very good, very close to authentic and the price for a Korean restaurant in Paris was quite ‚Äúaffordable‚Äù. The portions are big so it fills you well. It is a very popular restaurant so it gets crowded (even waiting lines outside) and there isn‚Äôt much space between tables. The staff is really nice and accommodating, if you need anything just ask and they will bring you.
Definitely recommend!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Korean dishes‚Äîtwo pages of choices. Love my spicy tofu soup. They need more vegetarian choices. The bibimbap bowl should be much hotter as the rice was room temperature so it made the dish less exciting.  Spartan furniture.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Newly opened. Very tasty in a nicely designed restaurant.

Food wise : we got the dish to share. Cheese + chicken, some KFC as well.
It‚Äôs all good. Loved the fried chicken with their honey soy sauce.
Of course, they‚Äôll let you take everything in takeaway if you don‚Äôt finish.

Service wise : they just opened, when it‚Äôs full it gets a bit slow but I‚Äôm sure they‚Äôll improve very soon.

Price wise : I found it very affordable for that kind of Korean cuisine, especially considering it‚Äôs located in the very center of Paris.

I do recommend it.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great prices and great location. Small menu. We got the KFC and Budae Jigae- KFC was great and crispy and juicy. Budae came with two rice and we added spice so that was great. Nice sauce and was not too bad, 7/10. Service was quick.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food looks delicious but is somehow tasteless.
The kimchi pancake is extra oily.
The service was nice and friendly.
Overall atmosphere is loud and fun, good for an affordable dinner with friends if you are in the area and don‚Äôt care much for the food quality.', 'rating': '4'}]

name: Flam&go
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "Very quant little Cafe. The decor is amazing. I had a gluten free soup that was lovely. They don't have a vegetarian option but they did have gluten free soup which was tasty... The green tea was lovely.
Wonderful atmosphere, very cozy and away from the rush in the stores..

The staff are young girls not very personable, so don't expect much from them but the place and food itself is lovely and definitely worth trying.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Nice place away from all the people. You have to order at the counter. As it was sunny, we enjoy our break outside. Too bad they had no espresso but the cakes were very good', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Cute little cafe to grab a quick bite‚Ä¶friendly people, beautiful views and great food‚Ä¶we had the svele and sognalapskaus‚Ä¶amazing!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Beautiful place, very cozy, wonderful views, and good bathroom. For a coffee place, it only has filtered coffee and no hot milk, and it wasn't very good. The cakes looked tasty but expensive. However, it has a wide range of dining dishes we didn't try.
Good peaceful place to hide from the rain, but coffee could be better.", 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Warm and cozy Kafe in middle of Fl√•m. It was the perfect ending to our trip to Fl√•m. We ordered some coffee, it was luke warm and when we asked for a hot coffee, the Kafe team was very friendly and served us hot coffee promptly and as a warm gesture we were offered chocholate cakes to make up for the coffee üòä', 'rating': '5'}]

name: BOOM BOOM VILLETTE
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Street Banh Mi at the Food Market. Follow a very good review of Vietnamese community group on Facebook, I gave it a try to support my homeland foods and restaurant owners. I tried their special ‚ÄúB√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o‚Äù which is kind of double price of a normal b√°nh m√¨ 8,5‚Ç¨. And that‚Äôs already expensive compared to many good banh m√¨ that I have tried in Paris. It was very noisy there and we needed to wait a bit long. And the ‚ÄúB√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o‚Äù is too far from the b√°nh m√¨ ch·∫£o that I know. Dry, no sauce and quantity is not up to the price 15‚Ç¨. The quality is average. And the bread is under baked, white, too soft not crunchy. I usually don‚Äôt spend time to write negative review. I did this time because it isn‚Äôt correct to serve average quality for high price.\nIt deserves 2,5 stars.', 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very well conceptualised food court with lots of of options. They have bars,burgers,Asian and Indian food. You can visit it before or after a movie as pathe gaumont is on the same building.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We came here to treat the kids to a morning of fun amidst a busy week of visits in Paris, lured by the prospect of lots of entertainment for them and a nice lunch in the food court. But when we got there, everything but the food court and the cinema was closed - apparently the kids activies won‚Äôt open before a couple of weeks. You would think that‚Äôs something worth mentioning on their website before having people trek all the way to La Villette for nothing! Yet another soulless place where the emphasis is making money. Such a let down.', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Kind of expensive for the small size of the portions and low quality of the food. It's just pre-made industrial food reheated in a fancy microwave priced like a normal restaurant. Not worth it.", 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Pokke restaurant at Boom Boom villette. Very slow service and they mixed up with our order and gave it to another person. Waited 30 minutes for one bowl.', 'rating': '2'}]

name: Maison Louvard
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "The crookie stole the show during my recent visit. This trendy fusion of croissant and cookie proved to be a flavorful delight, though a bit pricey for its size. While I didn't explore beyond this famed treat, the bakery's array of tempting options suggests it's a spot worth revisiting for those with a sweet tooth üòã", 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We called in for lunch and we were greeted by a very friendly waitress. We found the atmosphere to be excellent and very welcoming. Our waitress was very friendly and the food and service were superb. Braised beef cheek with seasonal vegetables and a terrine for starters were simply excellent. The wine was delicious too.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I tried the cookie croissant here few days ago. And it tastes as good as a regular croissant but 5 times more expensive, 7 times if you decide to take a table . Worth the hype? Not really.', 'rating': '2'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'ü§© crookie whaaaaat! I‚Äôve never had a cookie croissant ü•ê until today and I don‚Äôt think I can ever go back! Absolutely delicious, great cafe very vibrant and busy with lovely decor, perfect place to grab a morning coffee and treat!  As it‚Äôs quite popular service can be a bit slow but still well worth the visit', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "I saw this bakery on Social Media and was curious to know why people were given such a high rate to this place. I wanted to check it by myself üòâ The place is cozy and well decorated. The staff is super friendly and the 'viennoiserie' tasteful. The expresso is also really good and compared to other places in the capital, your getting a decent amount of coffee in your cup (not only a few drops). It was good, but wouldn't given them a 5 star rate (even if the bakker has apparently received an award recently). Guess I will have to go a second time (at lunch) to confirm my thoughts... A place to recommend anyhow.", 'rating': '4'}]

name: YSL Cafe
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Pretty busy for a Friday lunch. Great food, great service, nice restaurant.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Drinks were served very well. Great atmosphere', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The waitress wasn‚Äôt interested to take my order and then after 15 minutes when I have finally ordered she told me there are no ingredients and if I want to I can find myself something else.', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'it was a really nice place. you got the food really quick and the meat was brilliant it was perfectly cooked and perfectly seasoned\nwith salt and other nice flavors. If you live near by you shuld definitely go to eat lunch hear.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "The restaurant is small but well organized and the food is just great with affordable prices. It's an local place without an English menu and staff doesn't speak English so that's the only suggestion for the admin", 'rating': '4'}]

name: Une Kaak√© √† Paris
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "A Kaake √† Paris is a must-visit destination for those craving a delightful blend of Lebanese cuisine presented in a refreshing, modern fashion. The delectable flavors are simply outstanding, and the staff's warm and friendly demeanor elevates the entire dining experience. What's truly remarkable is that all of this comes at incredibly affordable prices, making it an exceptional value for the exquisite quality you receive.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Excellent Lebanese kaake in Paris, with friendly staff and high food quality. My favorite was the beef shawarma kaake; it's so juicy, and they are generous with the ingredients. Definitely a must-try!", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'had the best experience here!! the food is delicious and the service is even better, the guys here are so lovely and welcoming :)) will definitely be coming back! if I could, i would give 6 stars ü§©', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Everything is just so perfect! This is my first time trying kaag√© and i am impressed. Very generous portion and reasonable price. Also, it tastes fastastic, everything is fresh. Wonderful staff, they are super nice and welcoming.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'First and foremost, the staff at this place are incredibly friendly. Their warm welcome and attentive service set the stage for an enjoyable visit.
As for the food, we tried "la shawarma kaake" and "la kaake poulette," and we were blown away by how delicious they were.
From the kaake to the meat's flavor, transported me back to Lebanon. The exceptional taste left a lasting impression.
And can't forget about the generous portion sizes and the addition of "extra toum" without having to request it made the dining experience even more memorableü•¥

In conclusion, I am in love! I highly recommend ü§©', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Priv√© de dessert
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'This meal was a fun one! Each item looked like one thing but was entirely another thing! In addition to just the looks, it also tasted great overall with some good flavor twists as well! Some fennel in the polenta, a chestnut mash, etc.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'First time here and really enjoyed the experience! As other reviewers have mentioned, this is a concept restaurant where main dishes are disguised as desserts and vice versa.

Reservations are a must as the place is pretty small and the opening hours are odd.

A bit pricey, especially for the main dishes, but an experience nonetheless and one well worth it! All of the food is homemade and with fresh ingredients.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Here is an interesting concept: your savory dishes are crafted and dressed like desserts.
This restaurant is located in calm side street, close to the lively and busy Pigalle (plenty of bar options after dinner). The young service staff was attentive and reactive to our demands. They did take care of their customers as they set some portable heaters (I can't imagine how cold it could be without heaters).
On top of an interesting menu, there is a good selection of white and red wines -make sure to ask for recommendation if you are undecided.
Now comes what one comes for: the dishes that sound and look like dessert. Prior to the main event we tried the onion soup dressed as a cappuccino. The soup was oniony  but a bit too creamy and the consistency not thick enough. A  cheesy taste was also missing. The burger (and its three fries shaped like churros) was tasty: finally a burger with a really taste of meat! We would have like more fries, as only three (however big) are hard to share -we didn't find the dipping to be particularly good.
The floating island (ile flottante) was a combination of packed macaroni floating in the middle of a "mushroomy" sauce: make sure to sauce your macaroni bite or you'll get a very salty surprise. The fish (shaped as a pancake) was flaky and tasty.
While the main dishes were good, the desserts were a bit disappointing. The sole real dessert (the chocolate fondant) was delicious -the pineapple (shaped as fried breaded fish sticks coming with a strawberry grout) and the "pain perdu" were so-so and overpriced for the quantity in the plate.
Overall this place is worth a visit, and as suggested by its name, focus only on the main dishes!', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Lovely concept
Great service
Good food
In dessert my favorite was the oeufs plat', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We had a great time among friends. Very competent and friendly waitresses well described the dishes without spoiling the surprise. And even better she knew how to pair wine according to our orders and preferences.
Great experience!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Les d√©lices de Tunisie
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "Quite possibly the best sandwich I ever had in Paris, a dizzyingly complex combination of ingredients baked fresh to order. You might call it a Tunisian calzone or incorrectly refer to it as Casse-Cro√ªte or Fricassee, but in any case it's truly extraordinary and worth a special visit!", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great food. Unique tast.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Friday start with a few drinks at the "Demain c\'est loin" around the corner and when the hunger comes, this is the place to go ! the perfect season based product (even the bread !) is man made, delicious and just what you need for 5‚Ç¨ ! Also provide pizza to the just price (Senior 12‚Ç¨)', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious, healthy and clean food.\nThe personal are super cool and welcoming', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious, and in addition of sea food they have halal chicken', 'rating': '4'}]

name: Maison Ma√©
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "My partner couldn't go so I went alone but I loved this place. Went for the Sunday lunch and had a 7 course meal.  I was seated at the bar so I could watch all the food preparations. Everyone was extremely friendly and I loved every bite I had, which doesn't always happen with a tasting menu. Unquestionably recommended and truly a value as well.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Reviewer from Singapore.

This was hands down the best meal we had on our trip to Paris.

Chef Atsumi and his team gave us a stellar and unforgettable experience to say the least!

All in all each dish was expertly crafted and tasty. The flavors were fantastic. Well balanced and familiar but used in novel and exciting ways.

The marriage of French and Japanese culinary techniques and high quality ingredients made it accessible to us and made for a very scrumptious meal.

The atmosphere of the restaurant was warm and inviting we enjoyed the ambience, and it heightened the enjoyment of the meal as a whole.

My partner is not really a fan of pigeon as the taste of game is sometimes off putting to them. They were happy to accommodate and replaced the dish with Guinea Fowl which had a milder taste.

Per pax ‚Ç¨187/pax. We also had a truffle supplement for ‚Ç¨40 each.

We will definitely be back again when we‚Äôre back in Paris!

We look forward to dining here again and see great things ahead for chef Atsumi!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Exceeded my expectations! Perfect balance in each dish, with the scallop and dessert standing out. A bit noisy at peak times, but definitely worth the visit.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'üôÜ‍‚ôÄÔ∏èPROSüôÜ‍‚ôÄÔ∏è
üç¥ Fresh ingredients and great technique!! Beautifully presented too!

üôÖ‍‚ôÄÔ∏èCONSüôÖ‍‚ôÄÔ∏è
üßë‍üíºIt was an interesting gastronomical experience but the wait between each dish was too long. We were there for 3h and a half because we were in a rush but a typical dinner experience would‚Äôve lasted at least 4 hours. For the amount of dishes served, it was way too long. Specially since the portions were very small, almost bite size. We left still hungry.
üç¥Overall the food was good and sometimes unique but many dishes had an egg yolk base sauce or olive oil as a dominant flavor, thus some dishes felt repetitive taste wise.
\U0001fa91 I went with two tall friends and they said the tables weren‚Äôt very comfortable for their legs.', 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Stunning tasting menu with amazing wine Recommendations , the music and ambience are really calming , could seem a bit pricey but was totally worth it , it takes a while to finish everything but that‚Äôs exactly what I was looking for .
Also I had a dairy allergy and every supplements they gave me was perfect.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Bagels & Brownies
address_str: 12 Rue Notre Dame des Champs, 75006 Paris
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Bagelstein is a very kids friendly place with a very friendly and caring manager. We had a cappuccino and chocolate bagel here. It was a nice change from the typical brioche. The bagels are fresh and the coffee very froathy and fresh. The ambience has framed news articles of important Parisian moments in history. A great place to visit if you‚Äôre looking at something off radar or a takeaway', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent bagels for a good price. A new bagel benchmark for me. The staff are very nice üëç', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I realize that the first thing people think when they come to Paris is not "bagels", but try as I may my body just can\'t handle a coffee, a cigarette, and some cake for breakfast. So, while I realize it\'s a bit unorthodox, this was an excellent, excellent place to grab breakfast while in Paris. In fact, the meal was so good and nourishing that I started each and every day with an espresso and a bagel from here.\n\nThe manager was so accommodating, so friendly, and so warm--no matter how often I came in here and bothered him. Despite a modest language barrier, he made me feel very welcome and effortlessly made it easy to start my day right despite me not knowing a single word of French. Let\'s be honest: in the food capital of Europe, there are probably other places that are at the top of the list to visit while in Paris. Still, I have no doubt that if I ever make my way back to Paris, I\'ll be stopping by here to have a laugh with the manager while I custom make my own weird bagel sandwiches (without any judgments!)', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "The staff is really friendly to visitors and spoke English immediately when I told him that I don't speak French. The place is small but everything is functional; tables, food counter, bathroom.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A first in a bagelstein. I appreciate that they make a point of serving the bagels ü•Ø hot. Even when you take one from the refrigerated display case, they heat it up for you. Great üëç. The downside is that it still takes a little time. The small terrace is very nice but the tables were not cleaned.', 'rating': '3'}]

name: RAMEN WANG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "This is the most delicious ramen I have ever tasted in Paris. It reminds me of the ramen in Tokyo that I missed so much. Fast service, polite staff. Clean and comfortable. There may be a line outside, but it's worth the wait. I'm glad I found this place", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing place! Very good food and good service and fair prices. Every Tuesday they have vegan ramen. Would definitely come back', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved to eat with you. Just needed to wait some minutes outside. But was worth it!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I‚Äôve had ramen in Hong Kong and Tokyo and this is definitely one of my favourites of all time. We‚Äôve been several times, at different times of the day and days of the week yet the food has been amazingly consistent every single time.

The pork is their speciality and spectacular, every bite makes me so happy. The soup is always flavoursome and balanced.

Unfortunately they don‚Äôt take booking in advance so you have to queue. One time we went with our friends (~about 8 of us in total) after our wedding and we had to wait a long time as there was a lot of us but as the food was so tasty, people forgot about the long wait.

All of the staff are friendly, wonderful and attentive and it‚Äôs always a pleasure to come here.

While it‚Äôs growing in popularity, I hope it‚Äôll stay consistent and continue to be a gem in the 14th arrondissement.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Everything was delicious! Ramen was amazing with lots of flavors. The veggie gyozas as appetizers were tasty too. Nice variety of desserts and I really recommend the matcha financiers with ginger ice cream. Nice wine by the glass as well. Very cozy venue and ambience. A must!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: KINGKONG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We tried a few dishes. Considering everything was prepared very quickly. Fried chicken wings were spicy buy had a very nice sweet glaze, super crunchy. Tteokbokki had interesting flavors, tasted like tajin but with extra spice. Bibimbap was good, but the sauce was very mild.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This restaurant is quite well hidden in a small street near metro station Strasbourg Saint-Denis. By the look of the exterior I probably wouldn‚Äôt have entered had I not checked Google reviews before‚Ä¶ as the decor was somber and didn‚Äôt give an appetizing look to be honest.

However the food proved me wrong, we ordered lunch menu with the fried chicken as starter and bibimbap as main dish. The fried chicken was divine! So juicy and not greasy at all, the sweet and slightly spicy sauce blended perfectly with the batter, very delicious! The bibimbap itself was great too, it contained lots of ingredients especially vegetables, as they continued to cook in the stone ball they created a nice texture and taste together with the rice. I ordered the squid one, I should maybe have taken the beef and porc version as the squid was a bit chewy and not a lot of flavor. The other small negative point was probably that they were not very generous with the the pickled side dishes (see photo).

Overall I had a good dining experience and will definitely go back to try other dishes.

Update: we went back for the fried chicken and rice sticks, super delicious and you wouldn‚Äôt tell they were deep fried! Loved them.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really good place that serve authentic korean dishes!

Definitely a must take: the korean fried chicken, it was crispy and juicy.

Loved the kimchi fried rice with sea food, I would love to have some seaweed on it to be 100% matching with that I got in Korea!

Moreover great beer selection!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great place for late night eating or drinking, korean cuisine is not only about the bbq, kingkong is more like street style korean food with a nice atmosphere, kpop music and great customer service. The man (the owner maybe) was super friendly. Army stew was flavourful and very filling. I didn‚Äôt like the fried chicken very much, properly because of the sauce. The soft tofu stew (sundubu) is also average. All in all, great restaurant to try out and also their menu changes from time to time so it‚Äôs worth a comeback', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Unfortunately, they stopped serving their corndogs, but the food was delicious all the same! A nice Korean restaurant near Sentier, with a cool upstairs ambiance. Recommended!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Trantranzai
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Loved the decor & environment of the restaurant! At the time we arrived (around 6:30pm) the grilled dumplings weren‚Äôt available unfortunately so we took the shrimp steamed ones. It was good but I think it would‚Äôve been better grilled. In terms of noodles with soup, the portions are so big you are easily fulfilled ! Taste is good overall but the noodles were a bit dry even if it was in the soup. I would recommend though in terms of price/quantity/quality ratio it‚Äôs a win', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': '- Location is easy to access, walking distance to Metro & Bus stations.
- Nice service. It was quite busy at dinner.
- Noodles are excellent. The beef noodles are very tasty. The only point is that they serve with quite big amount.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "I love this atmosphere and design!!! It's not so often to see these decoration in China nowadays, but really have the feeling of walk into a film or go back to the last century. Food quality is top, i would recommend rice noodle.
. Service is perfect. Thank you and would come back again!!!", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Incredible Szechuan style noodles with authentic flavors. The atmosphere takes you straight to China, and we were seated very quickly despite the place being crowded. When you place your order, you can choose a spiciness level of 1-6. We ordered the beef noodles with level 4 spice, which was a perfect balance of flavor and spiciness. Service was on the slower side, but nothing to worry about.
Will definitely be visiting again.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': "When you step into this Chinese restaurant in Paris, it's as if you've been instantly transported to China. The ambiance is authentic, and the food is not only delicious but also generously portioned. It's a culinary journey worth experiencing.", 'rating': '5'}]

name: Keopi
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Went there early and got a table. One can scan the QR code to see the menu with pictures. Great service and friendly staff. Definitely good place for brunch.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious Korean brunch place! üá∞üá∑\U0001faf6üèº
We had to wait just a little bit for a table inside. It‚Äôs located in a little alley, easy to find if using Google maps.

Small menu but with lots of options!
We got the fried chicken, which tasted just perfect! Very soft on the inside and the seasonings was on point.
Salmon toast and salmon waffle which were both delicious.
The orange juice was very fresh and sweet.
Service was super fast! Friendly staff.
And most importantly, everything is HALAL!
(Expect for one thing which is the ‚Äúspam‚Äù)
Would definitely come back very soon!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'After watching their instagram account, I wanted to come here and try the brunch. It is an ‚Äúinstagramable‚Äù place, and as such, very popular so you‚Äôll have to wait. However, the waiting times are less than expected and it is worth it. The food is great and innovative. I had the waffle with fried chicken and it was delicious and abundant. The fried chicken is perfect and the sauce (sweet and spice) too, although it is not spicy.
The only problem was the time they took to bring our beverages. We ordered the homemade lemonade and we were almost finishing the dish when they brought it. We noticed the service of beverages is slow, so be patient.
In any case, I‚Äôd love to come back to try the sweet options.

üòãüåéüçΩÔ∏è‚úàÔ∏è
Sabor Kairos', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for brunch at 11:30 on a Sunday and waited for half an hour to be seated cause it was quite crowded. It was worth the wait though cause the staff were nice, service was alright and the food was delicious. We had waffles and they placed a bottle of maple syrup on every table.  I had rose tea and my friends had matcha flavoured drinks and they were all good. Reservations are not possible so avoiding peak times would be a good idea.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The location is simply great, not too far from the Grevin museum ! You really get to feel the parisian vibe.
The price was reasonable for a brunch + it was really delicious. The staff is also really nice and attentive.
We went for a kimchi and avocado salmon toast (which if you like salty and spicy kimchi is a perfect match with avocado and salmon). The Rose Latte was too die for with its hint of rose taste. The spicy chicken was really soft (a perfect boneless chicken if I dare say).
And for the dessert the waffle with matcha cream ! The cream paired perfectly with the fruits and the waffle ~ Beware though, the plate is kind of big so if you don‚Äôt have a big appetite it is best to share it.

All in all the pricing, the amount of food and the taste was more than worthy, a 10/10 for me.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: C√àPE ET FIGUE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We loved eating at this restaurant! I think we were lucky to get a table as it became very busy after we arrived. The food was delicious- very good quality. Even more exceptional was the service. They were very friendly and patient , despite our lack of French language skills. We later learned that it‚Äôs a family business, which just adds to the charm. Their set menu is good value for the quality of the dining experience.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent food and service. For appetizers we tried the burrata, escargots, and l‚Äô≈ìuf cocotte - all were great. For the main dish we got L‚Äôagneau - which was cooked 7 hours and tasted sublime (although I usually don‚Äôt eat much lamb). Le poulet and le boeuf bourguignon were amazing as well. The ambience is cozy and welcoming - best to reserve a table ahead of time as it tends to be busy.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing little restaurant in St Germaine. The food is some of the best we ate in the area. The staff are all charming and helped us with the translation as the menu has some great takes on traditional French cuisine.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Easily one of the best French restaurants in Paris. The dishes and the desserts are exceptional. Very affordable price for such high quality food. I recommend!
Food ordered: comme une poule au pot, agneau, fondant au chocolat, and crumble', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Of all the times I‚Äôve been in Paris, this is the best Parisian food I‚Äôve had. I found this place just like that and I didn‚Äôt regret it.

Me and my husband chose the three course menu (29‚Ç¨ great price!) and it was just heaven. The onion soup felt like a grandma soup, the lamb was so soft and tasty and the dessert was just amazing.

Please come to this place! The food and the service is great, very very recommended.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: La Piadineria
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'I guess it was alright. I ordered online the day before but when I came my order wasn‚Äôt ready so it was a bit frustrating. I chose the Ortolana with fries. It was ok it wasn‚Äôt really tasty, the goat cheese‚Äôs was all that was to it. It was quite flat and unsatisfying.\nBut if you want something quick enough to eat then you can come here it‚Äôs alright and quite cheap.', 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I am almost sure those reviews are fake. The food was absolutely horrible 0 flavors and 0 relation to italy. If i buy jambon and make a sandwich at home it will be 10 times more delicious and cheaper. Its a scam', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'GREAT FOOD. As an Italian, the food was just as back home. Super recommended!!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food on the go at unbeatable value for money in Paris. Surprised to find same quality of Italian stores also here :)\nWill get back!!!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really authentic Italian taste in a friendly and cozy atmosphere', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Fay‚Äôsi Tis
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I had dinner with my husband and we had a wonderful experience. Food was really good, portions are big and quality is over the top - with a perfect balance of spices and tastes. Service is equally pleasant and the atmosphere is cosy. A lot of attention to details which make this a very recommended place for dining. They also speak English, which is not mandatory but appreciated!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The service was terrible! Had a very rude waiter that kept asking us to leave at 9pm on the dot. You only have the table for 1.5hr and can‚Äôt stay 1 minute longer even if you‚Äôre just finishing your glass of wine. No one was waiting to be seated but still we were ran out of the restaurant. Would never go back because of this- better restaurants with a lot better service in the area!!', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Cute location, incredible food that is unique compared to classic parisian fare. Clean and well kept. Service staff were amazing but they were extremely busy so it took a while to get wine refills etc', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This place was sooo cozy!! The staff who worked there, the food and the music, such a good place!! I would recommend to everyone that‚Äôs visit Paris', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "The place is nice and the food is good

Service is slow and price are completely insane (20euros for literally a slice of eggplant: I really should have taken a picture it was hilarious).

Go there only if money is not an issue for you and you are ok with an average experience. Otherwise you'll be much better off in so one of many other restaurants in the area.", 'rating': '2'}]

name: Taco Mesa
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was incredible not only in taste but also in aesthetics. The freshness of the ingredients is unmistakable, and the proportions were just right. Tommy‚Äôs margarita and the churros are also a must try! If you miss authentic Mexican cuisine, this is definitely the place to go.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Authentic Mexican food.  Freshly made tortillas. My vegetarian tacos were very tasty and my daughter's birria tacos also great. The churros were superb. A little expensive but definitely will recommend.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'great atmosphere. came with a friend who knows mexican food. good portion of meat for al pastor & great flavour for quesadilla.\nprice for 3 tacos and a drink wasn‚Äôt cheap. took some time to wait for all three dishes since it got quite popular during peak hours.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I‚Äôm from California and was craving tacos so we went here and I‚Äôm so glad we did! Their Paloma and tacos were so good. I loved them all, especially the Birria one. Great service!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'BEST Tacos in Paris üåÆ!!taste and feel like Mexico!! üá≤üáΩ SOOOO good', 'rating': '5'}]

name: AC√Ä PIGALLE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Definitely worth coming here. At first we thought food was going to suck since they microwave a lot of the dishes but it was one of the best meals. Taco meat was so tasty and their burrito was 5/5! Would love to come back here again!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for dinner without reservation, but even tho they were packed, they were able to give us a table.
We got a liter of margarita to go with our Ac√† nachos. They were crisp and the topping was guacamole, some pulled meat and cheddar. Overall very tasty and yummy.
For the entrees we got burritos with different meats, and all of them were up to our expectations. The portion was also good, didn‚Äôt leave anyone hungry.
The only thing we noticed was that it took some time to get the attention of the waiter to order the entrees, but they were really packed and everyone was running around, so it‚Äôs understandable.
Recommended if you are around the Moulin Rogue.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Authentic Mexican food.
Relaxed atmosphere with great music.
Service attentive and friendly.
Very popular place at lunchtime.
No reservations possible at this time. Here it is first come, first served!', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really nice Tacos, a bit disappointed with my cantarito, which was adapted to Paris, a bit bitter instead sour and sweet. It is an amazing drink, anyway that you should try citric, refreshing and their version bitter.  I loved my nachos and my governor tacos(prawn).
The horchata will be 100% better if you make it natural.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Overall, is a good place to eat tacos considering you are in Paris. Formule of three tacos for 10‚Ç¨ is a great option. Good flavor in the barbacoa, pastor a little dry, and carnitas would improve with a little more coriander. Sauces are good and tasty, not super spicy. Agua de horchata is super good, not too sweat which I like.  However, the dessert, the pastel de tres leches, falls short of expectations. While sweet and pastry-like, it lacks the authentic essence of a true pastel de tres leches.', 'rating': '4'}]

name: Marvely
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was amazing! We don‚Äôt speak French and our server spoke enough English to help. I would recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris. I‚Äôm already wanting to return to try something else!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Hello brunchy people, if you're looking for a place to take brunch you might somehow be lucky.

Apart from waiting from 1 hour and 20 mins outside the place is good and the food is good. The ambience is a bit like a coffee shop no music in the background and people whispering.

I took the brioche perdue mouth watering and tasty with salted caramel, this is my to go in such places

Would do it again but have to avoid the long wait!", 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Never had such a good brunch before. Amazing service, friendly staff and the fooood!!! Try the Beef Toast üòç', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'What a complete gem!  Best family oriented place we ate in Paris or London.  A must stop for breakfast, lunch, or light dinner in Paris.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best brunch in Paris. The staff is super friendly and caring. Food is original and very tasty. Service is fast! Location is very pink and girly üò¨', 'rating': '5'}]

name: CHEZ HAKI
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "Went with my girlfriend; we enjoyed the ravioli and Nems starters, both worth trying.

Unfortunately, the main dishes fell short. The Poulet Croustillant noodles lacked flavor, were excessively greasy, and the chicken was merely okay.

Riz loc-lac had dry rice, chewy beef, mainly fat.

Hoping to give the benefit of the doubt, we visited at 4 PM, but suspect the dishes weren't freshly made‚Äîmicrowave sounds and quick service raised concerns.", 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Good overall, good quality-price ratio, vegetarian lamen did not reach the highest expectations (noodles were very good, the broth could have a bit more flavor), but very large portion size, and definitely better than a lot of places in France.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We discovered this restaurant while on a walk and decided to try right then and there. The gyoza was fab and we also enjoyed the soup ramen. I ordered the fried chicken cutlet noodles for myself but the serving was pretty big and would actually be enough for two people. We shall return.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very busy Chinese restaurant with nice expedite staff and extremely fast turnaround. Food was good and overall a very authentic Chinese restaurant experience.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was incredible. Tender noodles with the perfect chew with rich delicious broth. We loved the S7! The service was excellent and the atmosphere cozy. A perfect rich and hearty meal at very reasonable prices especially for the flavor, portions, and quality.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Mopa
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "Really atmospheric vegan place ‚Äì\xa0I docked a star because the burger was good, but not the most amazing vegan burger ever. Good fries, friendly staff ‚Äì but lots of stuff wasn't available from menu on a Saturday night.", 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Awesome vegan place with really filling and tasty food! We tried the arancini, cold beast burger, and doner kebab. The portions were very filling and the flavors were incredible. Can‚Äôt wait to come back!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Very nice place with friendly staff and tasty food. Can't wait to try the brunch!", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "The service and interaction alone with the server was top notch. He even gave me a charger to top up my battery. I instantly felt welcome in this small but cosy environment. I didn't know how to eat my Kebap initially but once I figured out my technique, it was a sumptuous mix of soft bread filled with awesome delicacies.\nThe cheesecake was the perfect way to end this beautiful meal which I accompanied with a chai latte. Mind you, Mopa are not big on sugar, which is perfect for me but not to everyone's taste, so do ask whether any supposed sweet item you order has sugar in it already.\nHighly recommended whenever you visit Paris or just want to try something different. The nuggets will freak you out, so lookout to be blown away. Okay. Enjoy.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "What an awesome find this place is! Last dinner of my staying in Paris at Mopa was amazing. If you want to experience a true taste adventure, especially to the vegan foods I highly recommend eating here! They have %100 organic vegan food and burger. Very cool and friendly service. Super cozy and cute place, a real crush for the really super good bite! This place truly ‚Äúa must ‚Äú for the plant-based peeps in your posse!  Loved every bite. Don't miss this restaurant if you're visiting Paris.", 'rating': '5'}]

name: GYOZA HOUSE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Most creative gyozas I tried in Paris.
Truly a wonderful cuisine served near Opera. It is this kind of dish which gives you a happy day! It‚Äôs also affordable given the quality which you get.
Highly highly recommend to go.
I recommend the shiitake veggie gyoza which will make you melt ‚ú®', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved the food and the wide selection. Great presentation, atmosphere, decoration and eating experience. However difficult to see the difference of which flavor gyoza was which when served. Music choice was very pleasant.
There were unfortunately  two flickering lights which was distracting.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good gyozas and lots of choices. Super friendly staff and cute setting.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Gyoza ü•ü coconut chicken filling was good.  If you are from East Asia, you probably won't be satisfied by some of the taste, however, It's quite interesting to try 8 flavour gyoza in one go üòä", 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'For me, it‚Äôs easy. If you feel like eating gyozas, you need to come to this place.

It‚Äôs the best gyozas you can find in the city.

The service is nice and very polite.

You won‚Äôt be disappointed. I highly recommend.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Land & monkeys
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Absolutely delightful dining experience. Visited here as a birthday treat and was blown away by the food. 8 course tasting meal with an extra little sweet treat at the end. The staff were very friendly and helpful and I thoroughly enjoyed each course, nothing I didn‚Äôt enjoy. Each course was explained by the waiter and it was also very interesting to learn that they produce very minimal waste here as they use every little bit in some way whether added into a sauce or used as a glaze. I‚Äôve been vegan for 2 years and vegetarian for many many years and this is honestly some of the best food I‚Äôve ever eaten. Will definitely visit again. I also thought ¬£55 for the meal was more than reasonable for the quality of food. Nice little touch to have a birthday card for me on the table too.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was creative and tasted fantastic. Everything was vegan too. Every course brought to our table was more delicious than the previous one. The staff were friendly and thoroughly explained each dish brought to our table. The interior of the restaurant was clean and had a nice vibe. I highly recommend this place for a date night or celebration. I‚Äôm not sure if they have earned any Michelin Stars, but they deserve one if not!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Flavoursome dining experience and attentive/kind staff. We really enjoyed our evening here, the food from start to finish was spectacular with interesting flavours and immaculate presentation! We ended up spending 2.5 hours in the restaurant, leaving with a huge smile on our face‚Ä¶ worth the ¬£.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was great and very good value for money and wine pairing really worked so no complaints on that front and well worth a visit. However please put a curtain around the entrance so you don‚Äôt get hit with an icy blast every time the door is opened . It‚Äôs simply and everywhere in Europe . Second and most disappointing please don‚Äôt rush me out the door when I‚Äôm having my digestive. I‚Äôve enjoyed a good meal I‚Äôm relaxing and I want to end my meal comfortably. This was not just us but everyone was rushed out to make way for the second siting . Adjust your course timings don‚Äôt simply say sorry we have our next sitting coming. And finally 2  to 3 tables too many in this small restaurant making it a little more cramped and less personal than I would have liked . Still a great meal though.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'What an excellent experience! We had the 8 course dining experience and it was just phenomenal. We‚Äôve been vegan for 8 years now and have never eaten such imaginative, creative and delicious food before. This is another level of genius. We also enjoyed the wine pairing, which was a delightful accompaniment to each course. Would highly recommend to all so you can experience the extensive range of what can be done with just plants!! Our minds were left blown.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Marcus Pizze Amore
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'My favorite Pizzeria. This Pizzeria has a lot of vegan options which makes it perfect when I‚Äôm looking for a place to go with my friends. They even have delicious vegan dessert options (vegan Tiramis√π, vegan Nocciola Calzone and vegan Pizza bread sticks with Nocciola ü§§).

This time I had a vegan Margherita and the Pizza sticks with Nocciola as take away for lunch. It tasted great as always and the team was super friendly.

I really like how the place looks like. It is small and cosy. Definitely great to eat there. It gets packed quickly so come early if you want to be sure to get a table! üòÑ', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Definitely the best vegan pizza in Paris. Some of the best I've tried anywhere in the world, actually! They need to open an all-vegan restaurant!!", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Went here for lunch and have no regrets. It‚Äôs one of the best pizzas, let alone vegan pizzas, I‚Äôve ever had. My brother also loved his margarita pizza.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "The pizza was great & the people even better, i personally enjoyed the 'Tortufo' vegan pizza which was totally incredible & girlfriend had a margarita which also was delicious.

I'd recommend going with vegan pizza! üëçüëç", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super friendly staff and AMAZING vegan pizza. The vegan tiramisu was also amazing. Would 10/10 eat here again!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Green Farmer's Paris
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We got takeaway here and I was super impressed with all the food. The burgers were juicy and more ish, the nuggets had a great crisp and the fish n chips was a massive portion. The Smash Truffle really stood out, such a great flavour. I really enjoyed it and would love to go back and eat in the restaurant too!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Staff was very nice (spoke some English which was super helpful understanding the menu). Inside is kind of small but still enough seating and some outside of a busy street. The food was pretty tasty. I wasn't a big fan of the sauces they made in house, but they have a wide range of them for you to try. Also tried one of their canned beverages. Again not the biggest fan but if you like soda I think you will like. Would recommend and come back to try more of their vegan options.", 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'So thrilled to see yet another fabulous vegan eaterie in France. I had the green fish burger and it had a fabulous texture!  Topped with tartare in a brioche bun why do we even need to risk people lives in order to plunder our oceans?!!ü§∑üèº‍‚ôÄÔ∏è. Just lovely, lovely, lovely. If you‚Äôre vegan or not then get your butts in this establishment as there‚Äôs a great choice.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We were in a hurry to the Moulin Rouge after missing a dinner reservation. The server fit us in and got our food in time! The burgers were beyond delicious! And the service was phenomenal! Definitely recommend', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best vegan burgers ever! If you feed this to a non vegetarian, for sure he will not notice ü§´

I got the chichen burger and I loved it! Onion rings were too greasy though.
The truffle mayo sauce was wow!

It‚Äôs great that this place is open even between lunch and dinner when many restaurants close. üéâ', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Kous
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I happened to stop by this place by coincidence and I am happy I did. The place is small and the food is good. I tried the Tanjia couscous and I did love it. This is important as I am not a couscous person by default and hate the exaggerated spices or the pool of liquids on my food. The staff are polite and attentive.

What caught my eye was the level of anticipations to the needs of clients

1- You can chose size of your plate, depending how hungry you are.

2- for first time I saw in my life that a restaurant also includes feminine hygiene pad also in the toilet.

Bravo for that , a good customer service wins .

I do recommend the place for those whom like to have a nice healthy food. I will eat there again while am in Paris.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent couscous!  Several offerings. Vegetarian, meats, vegan. Choices of classic or whole wheat grain (couscous). Super fresh. Delicious mint tea & small North African pastries. Friendly service. Lovely setting in a modern North African style. Try it. You will not regret it.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "We're always a fan of Morrocan cuisine, and KOUS did not disappoint. Try the soup before your main dish, and get a cup of hot tea - you'll be glad you did.", 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very pleasant place to eat a good, satisfying couscous, delicious mint tea and pastry and very tasty appetizer. The staff is very welcoming and obliging. I will definitely go back.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'So good', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Kous
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'This "bar" is a take-away for couscous.
The choice of vegetables and meats is wide and the quality excellent.
However, like everything in Paris the prices are relatively steep.
For 3 persons, couscous with mixed meats, will cost about 45 Euro.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Marocco food is amazing and also cheap for size M ‚Ç¨14 u can share also( I‚Äôm Asian so for me the portion is quite big );) it‚Äôs good for health and diet. Recommend place for lunch', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very tasty and fast couscous at a reasonable price! The lamb one (Tanjia) in particular is delicious! Perfect place for lunch breaks', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This place was THE BEST! I met the owner Bader and he was super nice. A must try if you‚Äôre in Paris!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'They have been their for over 6 years worth a visit!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Afri Call Food
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent food. Balanced spices. Beautiful ingredients. Friendly service.  Best meal we had in paris', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really nice experience the food is good', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super ! 10/10', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super üëç', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super experience!!!!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Afrodisiac Paris 2
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Real West-African food. Very good. I have been there three times. One time, lamb. Second time fish with rice. Last time fish with banana. Very tasteful. People are very friendly.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'my boyfriend comes from Senegal and we would like to visit some nice african restaurant in Paris. After searching google we found this restaurant. Looks very sophisticated with tasteful decor.

real world was totally different.
- we had to sit very narros between other customers, event though the service person didn¬¥t ask us whether it is fine for us.

- for washing my hands
the WC is the highlight, no sope, toilet paper around without fixing, dirty in side, smells like drain. the restaurant was not busy at all, but no one cares about it. I already lost my appetite.

- food
was not warm enough, I had seafood grill plate. the corn was bad so I spitted out and very salty.

the price range is quite high, so I would never ever visit this restaurant with that price.

Please go others.', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Good food , bad service . They run out of beef and brought fish pastel to my friend without asking , not enough variety of dessert. They don‚Äôt take credit card', 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great african food  the only reason why its not a 5 star is because the food is way too expensive for the small portion served. Not enough food per dish!!', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food was fantastic and the staff was really helpful. Nice upscale decor.', 'rating': '5'}]

name: Wakanda factory Paris nation
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Round of applause üôå this place blew my mind. Firstly the food. 10/10 flavourful, well cooked and huge portions. I have never seen so much ripe plantain in my life. Juicy and just so on point. The decor was fitting, well done and tasteful. I feel to return to Paris just for this food.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Quaint, vibrant, and intimate restaurant that is full of Afro Flavor. A bit of heat, salt, acidity, balanced to perfection. My experience with Bakary the host was exceptional, he ensured I received the highest quality of service. I will definitely return to this restaurant and recommend you try their numerous meal selections!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I was in Paris for 4 days and I casually found this place. I ordered dinner twice: soooo good. Big portions, very tasty, cool place and also not expansive! Recommend it!!!!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Tasty food and big serving portions.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Welcoming place with easy going vibes. They serve big portion of delicious food', 'rating': '5'}]
